annotationA: Protein elav; Required for the proper development and maintenance of neurons presumably by affecting RNA metabolism
annotationB: DNA-binding protein Ewg; May function as a positive regulator of transcription in developing and differentiated neurons, regulating common aspects of neuronal differentiation and maintenance. Requirement in the CNS may be higher than in the peripheral system. Vital for development of the indirect flight muscles; Belongs to the NRF1/Ewg family
